### <a id="inverses-of-setoid-functions">Inverses of setoid functions</a>

We define a data type that represent the semantic concept of the *image* of a function
(cf. the [Setoid.Overture.Inverses][] module of the [agda-algebras][] library).

\begin{code}

module _ {ùë® : Setoid Œ± œÅ·µÉ}{ùë© : Setoid Œ≤ œÅ·µá} where
 open Setoid ùë© using ( _‚âà_ ; sym ) renaming ( Carrier to B )

 data Image_‚àã_ (f : ùë® ‚ü∂ ùë©) : B ‚Üí Type (Œ± ‚äî Œ≤ ‚äî œÅ·µá) where
  eq : {b : B} ‚Üí ‚àÄ a ‚Üí b ‚âà (f ‚ü®$‚ü© a) ‚Üí Image f ‚àã b

\end{code}

An inhabitant of `Image f ‚àã b` is a dependent pair `(a , p)`, where `a : A` and
`p : b ‚âà f a` is a proof that `f` maps `a` to `b`.  Since the proof that `b`
belongs to the image of `f` is always accompanied by a witness `a : A`, we can
actually *compute* a (pseudo)inverse of `f`. For convenience, we define this
inverse function, which we call `Inv`, and which takes an arbitrary `b : B` and
a (witness, proof)-pair, `(a , p) : Image f ‚àã b`, and returns the witness `a`.

\begin{code}

 Inv : (f : ùë® ‚ü∂ ùë©){b : B} ‚Üí Image f ‚àã b ‚Üí Carrier ùë®
 Inv _ (eq a _) = a

 InvIsInverse ≥ : {f : ùë® ‚ü∂ ùë©}{b : B}(q : Image f ‚àã b) ‚Üí (f ‚ü®$‚ü© (Inv f q)) ‚âà b
 InvIsInverse ≥ (eq _ p) = sym p

\end{code}

`InvIsInverse ≥` proves that `Inv f` is the range-restricted right-inverse of the setoid function `f`.


### <a id="injective-and-surjective-setoid-functions">Injective and surjective setoid functions</a>

If `f : ùë® ‚ü∂ ùë©` is a setoid function from `ùë® = (A , ‚âà‚ÇÄ)` to `ùë© = (B , ‚âà‚ÇÅ)`, then
we call `f` *injective* provided `‚àÄ (a‚ÇÄ a‚ÇÅ : A)`, `f ‚ü®$‚ü© a‚ÇÄ ‚âà‚ÇÅ f ‚ü®$‚ü© a‚ÇÅ` implies `a‚ÇÄ ‚âà‚ÇÄ a‚ÇÅ`;
we call `f` *surjective* provided `‚àÄ (b : B)`, `‚àÉ (a : A)` such that `f ‚ü®$‚ü© a ‚âà‚ÇÅ b`.
We codify these definitions in Agda and prove some of their properties
inside the next submodule where we first set the stage by declaring two
setoids `ùë®` and `ùë©`, naming their equality relations, and making some
definitions from the standard library available.

\begin{code}

module _ {ùë® : Setoid Œ± œÅ·µÉ}{ùë© : Setoid Œ≤ œÅ·µá} where
 open Setoid ùë® using () renaming ( _‚âà_ to _‚âà‚ÇÅ_ ; Carrier to A )
